name: GE90 Roar | KLM Boeing 777-300ER Taxi and Takeoff from Calgary Airport
description:
Always nice to see the world's largest twinjet here, especially in KLM blue! Here we have PH-BVK, one of KLM's Boeing 777-300ERs taxiing up close and making an intersection departure off runway 17L with an amazing spool up sound! ATC is included, hope you enjoy.

Thanks for watching!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

FLIGHT INFORMATION
Airline: KLM Royal Dutch Airlines (KLM/KL)
Aircraft: Boeing 777-306/ER (B77W)
Flight Number: KL678
Aircraft Name: Yellowstone National Park / Nationaal Park Yellowstone 
Livery: Old
Engines: 2x GE90-115B
Registration: PH-BVK
Route: Calgary (YYC) - Amsterdam-Schiphol (AMS)
Callsign: KLM 678 heavy
Runway used: 17L from Zulu
Date filmed: April 28, 2018
Local time: 1520
